<Page x:Class="TEFL_App.Views.Course.Modules.Mod4Part2"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006" 
      xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008" 
      xmlns:local="clr-namespace:TEFL_App.Views.Course.Modules"
      mc:Ignorable="d" 
      d:DesignHeight="450" d:DesignWidth="800"
      Title="Module 4 - Part 2">

    <Grid  x:Name="Mod4Chapter2Grid" Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterGrid}" >

        <Grid.RowDefinitions>
            <RowDefinition Height="Auto" />
            <RowDefinition Height="*" ScrollViewer.CanContentScroll="True"/>
        </Grid.RowDefinitions>
        <Grid.ColumnDefinitions>
            <ColumnDefinition/>
        </Grid.ColumnDefinitions>

        <TextBlock Grid.Row="0" Grid.Column="0" Text="Module 4, Part 2: Final Guidance Notes" Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterTitle}"/>
                
        <ScrollViewer x:Name="ScrollArea" Grid.Row="1" Grid.Column="0" >
            <StackPanel Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterPageArea}">



                <RichTextBox x:Name="mod4part2sect1" Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionText}">
                    <RichTextBox.Effect>
                        <DropShadowEffect BlurRadius="20"  Color="Gray" Direction="315"/>
                    </RichTextBox.Effect>
                    <FlowDocument>
                        <Paragraph   Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionTitle}">
                            4.2.1 The Final Exam
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            The
                            <Hyperlink Click="FinalExamPage_Click">
                                Final Exam
                            </Hyperlink> 
                            consists of 50 multiple choice questions based on the content detailed in this course.</Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            To pass the exam, you must obtain a score of at least 70%. The exam grading is automatic, and each attempt is saved against your profile.
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            After completing the exam, you will be able to submit your Lesson Plan Assignment for marking by one of our tutors.
                        </Paragraph>
                    </FlowDocument>


                </RichTextBox>


                <RichTextBox x:Name="mod4part2sect2" Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionText}">
                    <RichTextBox.Effect>
                        <DropShadowEffect BlurRadius="20"  Color="Gray" Direction="315"/>
                    </RichTextBox.Effect>

                    <FlowDocument>
                        <Paragraph  Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionTitle}">
                            4.2.2 The Lesson Plan Assignment
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            After completing the Final Exam, you will be able to submit your assessed lesson plan via the
                            <Hyperlink x:Name="LessonPlanLink" Click="LessonPlanLink_Click">
                                Lesson Plan Assignment section
                            </Hyperlink>
                            page.
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            Refer to Module 2, Part 2 to refresh yourself on how to prepare a lesson.
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            When you feel ready, select the age group you aim to teach in your first assignment as teacher of English as a foreign language. Here at the North American TEFL Academy, we want you to develop the direction you aim to go, whether that is as a kindergarten teacher or a high school teacher. Please find a lesson topic you feel you are both comfortable with and one that is realistic.
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph Style="{StaticResource TEFLParagraphTitle}">
                            Some suggestions
                        </Paragraph>
                        <List>
                            <ListItem Style="{StaticResource SpacedListItem}">
                                <Paragraph>
                                    <Bold>For Kindergarten:</Bold> Animals, food, colors and shapes
                                </Paragraph>
                            </ListItem>
                            <ListItem Style="{StaticResource SpacedListItem}">
                                <Paragraph>
                                    <Bold>For Grade School:</Bold> Greetings, geography, school
                                </Paragraph>
                            </ListItem>
                            <ListItem Style="{StaticResource SpacedListItem}">
                                <Paragraph>
                                    <Bold>Young Adult:</Bold> Expressing ideas and emotions, describing the family, career aspirations
                                </Paragraph>
                            </ListItem>
                            <ListItem Style="{StaticResource SpacedListItem}">
                                <Paragraph>
                                    <Bold>Adult:</Bold> Office environment, current issues, business etiquette
                                </Paragraph>
                            </ListItem>
                        </List>
                        <Paragraph>
                            You can refer to the following template for guidance:
                            <Hyperlink NavigateUri="https://echinacareers.com/Downloads/Planning%20a%20Lesson%20-%20Template.docx"
                                       RequestNavigate="Hyperlink_RequestNavigate">
                                Planning a Lesson - Template.docx
                            </Hyperlink>
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            Before you can submit your assignment, you must first complete the Final Exam.
                        </Paragraph>
                    </FlowDocument>
                </RichTextBox>

                <RichTextBox x:Name="mod4part2sect3" Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionText}">
                    <RichTextBox.Effect>
                        <DropShadowEffect BlurRadius="20"  Color="Gray" Direction="315"/>
                    </RichTextBox.Effect>

                    <FlowDocument>
                        <Paragraph  Style="{StaticResource TEFLChapterSectionTitle}">
                            4.2.3 Conclusion
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            <Bold>Congratulations!</Bold>
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            After you have completed the Final Exam and passed your lesson plan assignment, the course will be complete.
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            You will receive a digital copy of your TEFL certificate.
                        </Paragraph>
                        <Paragraph>
                            Your certificate code will always be available online via the
                            <Hyperlink x:Name="TEFLVerifyLink" RequestNavigate="Hyperlink_RequestNavigate">
                                eChinaCareers TEFL Verify
                            </Hyperlink>
                            page
                        </Paragraph>
                    </FlowDocument>
                </RichTextBox>

            </StackPanel>
        </ScrollViewer>
    </Grid>
</Page>
